## 10. Cross-Workflow Non-Functional Requirements

All workflows in this register should be implemented with the following platform requirements in mind:

### Security
- backend-enforced access control
- database-level read/write rules
- secure file access
- role and scope enforcement
- sensitive-action auditing

### Reliability
- idempotent external event processing
- retryable async jobs
- queued heavy processing
- graceful failure states
- monitoring and alerting

### Observability
- structured event logging
- workflow-level metrics
- conversion and failure funnels
- admin/ops dashboards
- traceability for user-impacting failures

### UX Consistency
- clear success/failure states
- preserved return paths after auth/upgrade
- transparent access-denied messaging
- no dead-end screens
- async job visibility where relevant

### Compliance
- consent tracking
- retention and archival controls
- export/deletion request handling
- activity audit history
- controlled use of PII and company-sensitive records

